A vintage 1950s-style illustration of a frustrated man in a mid-century living room, surrounded by tangled telephone cords that snake across the floor and wrap around furniture. He sits in an armchair holding an old rotary telephone receiver, staring at a stack of identical formal letters piling up on his coffee table like an avalanche. Through the window, a gleaming modern transmission tower is visible but impossibly far away on the horizon. The color palette features muted mustards, teals, and warm browns typical of vintage advertising art. The man's expression conveys weary determination mixed with exasperation, capturing the endless bureaucratic loop of trying to get a simple answer from a large corporation.
